attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (FreeBSD), dynamically linked, interpreter /libexec/ld-elf.so.1, for FreeBSD 8.4, not stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This is a backdoor for FreeBSD systems. The malware establishes a persistent connection to a command and control (C2) server, collects extensive system information (OS, CPU, memory, network, processes), and exfiltrates it. It then enters a loop to receive and execute remote commands, which include providing a reverse shell via `/bin/sh`, arbitrary command execution, file uploading/downloading, file deletion, and process termination. It uses a file at `/usr/sbin/config.bak` likely for configuration or to flag its presence. Key IOCs include the C2 domain `alibaba.zzux.com` and fallback IP `119.28.139.20` on port 443.
